## `Ai` — Claude calls (see `rails_ai.mdc`)

### Text

```ruby
text = Ai.ask("Summarize margin risk.", system: AnalystService::SYSTEM_PROMPT)

text = Ai.chat(
  messages: [{ role: "user", content: "..." }],
  system: AnalystService::SYSTEM_PROMPT,
  max_tokens: 4096
)
```

### JSON

```ruby
payload = Ai.json(
  system: AnalystService::SYSTEM_PROMPT,
  keys: %i[summary key_findings recommendations risk_flags lender_narrative],
  defaults: { key_findings: [], recommendations: [], risk_flags: [] },
  messages: [
    { role: "user", content: "Farm context:\n#{context.to_json}" },
    { role: "user", content: "Generate a lender summary." }
  ]
)
# => { summary: "...", key_findings: [...], ... }
```

- Pass **`prompt:`** OR **`messages:`**, not both.
- Strips markdown code fences; on parse failure uses `defaults` (plural keys default to `[]`).
- Errors: `Ai::ConfigurationError` (missing API key), `Ai::ApiError` (Anthropic failure).

### Model

- Default: latest stable Sonnet (`claude-sonnet-4-6`).
- Override: `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` in `.env` → `AppConfig.anthropic_model`.

