## `RescuesAi` — controller error handling

**Rule:** AI controllers `include RescuesAi` instead of inline `rescue` blocks.

```ruby
class Api::V1::AnalystMessagesController < BaseController
  include RescuesAi
  # ...
  private

  def ai_failure_message
    "Analyst request failed."  # optional override; default shown above
  end
end
```

| Exception | HTTP | `errors[].field` |
|-----------|------|------------------|
| `Ai::ConfigurationError` | 503 | `anthropic` (exposes config message) |
| `Ai::ApiError` | 502 | `anthropic` (generic `ai_failure_message`) |

Used by: `AnalystMessagesController`, `AnalystReportsController` (override message: `"Report generation failed."`).

