## `ApiTestHelpers` — integration tests

Included globally via `api/test/test_helper.rb`.

```ruby
auth = register_user!
headers = api_headers(auth[:token])

post "/api/v1/farms", params: { farm: { name: "Test", ... } }, headers: headers, as: :json
assert_api_success(:created)

token = login_user!(email: "farmer_one@fieldmark.test")  # fixture user
```

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `api_headers(token)` | JSON + optional Bearer |
| `json_body` / `api_data` / `api_errors` | Parse `{ data, meta, errors }` envelope |
| `assert_api_success(:created)` | Assert status, empty errors, data present |
| `register_user!` | Random email register → `{ email, password, token }` |
| `with_stubbed_service(Klass, :call, value) { ... }` | Stub class method for jobs/services |

**Rules:**

- Stub `AnalystReportGeneratorService` (or other Claude services) in tests — **never** call Claude in CI.
- Use `perform_enqueued_jobs` after POST report to run `GenerateAnalystReportJob` inline (test adapter).
- User fixtures must include `email`, `encrypted_password`, `jti` (see `test/fixtures/users.yml`).

Example: `api/test/integration/api_smoke_test.rb`

